Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Cut the @lime{1} into wedges. Pick the @mint{1%bunch} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Pop the potatoes onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%grams}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, crack the @egg{1} into a #medium bowl{} and whisk.

Put the @panko breadcrumbs{50%grams} into another medium bowl, add the @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet}, then season with @pepper{} and the @salt{1/4%tsp} for the breadcrumbs.

Season the @British chicken thighs{4}, then dip it into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to coat the bottom of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan and fry until golden-brown, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Transfer the chicken to a baking tray and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{8-11%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken bakes, drain the @king prawns{150%grams}.

Discard the oil from the frying pan and wipe clean. Pop back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the prawns, @red Thai style paste{50%grams} and @honey{15%grams}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir-fry for ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat. Transfer the prawns and sauce to a medium bowl.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Pour the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing into the bowl of prawns.

Add a squeeze of lime juice, the chopped mint and @coleslaw mix{120%grams}. Stir to combine, then set aside.

When everything's ready, plate up your fried chicken with the prawn salad and sesame wedges alongside.

Serve with the lime wedges and @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} on the side. Enjoy!